===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|ろく|yomi=goon|alt=碌}}

Originally referred to "flat" in reference to flat {{m|en|land}}, in turn the core meaning of the kanji character.<ref name="KDJ2">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2|陸・碌}}</ref><ref name="DJR"/>

The alternative {{m|ja|碌}} spelling is an example of [[ateji]].<ref name="KDJ2"/><ref name="DJR"/><ref name="DDJS">{{R:Digital-Daijisen}}</ref><ref name="SMK5"/>

First attested in the {{m|ja||羅葡日辞書|tr=Ra-Ho-Nichi Jisho|Latin-Portuguese-Japanese Dictionary}} of 1595.<ref name="KDJ2"/>

====Pronunciation====
